\f0\b\fs58 \cf2 Heirloom Key Lime Pie Recipe
\fs56 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\ql\qnatural

\fs48 \cf2 Ingredients
\fs38 \

\fs40 \
Crust
\b0 \

\fs46 1-1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs\
1/3 cup sifted confectioners' sugar\
6 Tablespoon unsalted butter, melted and cooled
\fs40 \

\b Filling\

\b0\fs46 4 large egg yolks\
1 (14-oz.) can sweetened condensed milk\
1/2 cup key lime juice, divided\
1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar
\fs44 \

\b\fs40 Topping\

\b0\fs46 4 egg whites
\b \

\b0 1/4 cup sugar
\fs42 \

\fs40 \

\b\fs50 Directions
\fs38 \

\b0\fs44 In a bowl, combine 1-1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sifted confectioners' sugar, and 6 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and cooled.\
Press the mixture into a pie plate to form a crust.  Bake in a 350-degree-F oven for 10 minutes until lightly browned.\
Cool on rack. \
Beat 4 egg yolks until light in color, stir in one 14-ounce can sweetened condensed milk, 1/4 cup lime juice, 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar, then another 1/4 cup lime juice.  Spoon into shell and bake at 325 degrees F. until it sets, about 10 to 15 minutes.  Freeze for at least 3 hours. \
\
Beat 4 egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff. Spread over pie, and bake in 450 degree F. oven until meringue is golden.\
