\b\fs56 \cf2 Origin and History of Key Lime Pie
\fs46 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf2 The first Key Lime Pie was created in the 1850's. There were very few cows on the Keys of Florida in those days. The advent of sweetened condensed milk in 1856 was a real boon to the residents of the Keys. \
It was a natural reaction to combine the new product with the limes into a pie. The original pies had a pastry crust, of course, but the graham cracker crust dates back at least to 1949. \
